[According to the data on the Worldometer website, the total number of cases of COVID-19 worldwide is 4 180 303, with reports of cases by 216 countries and territories worldwide. The total number of confirmed cases reported from outside China now represents 98.0% of the total number of reported cases. The epicenter has shifted outside of China to Western Europe and the USA. The USA, with more than 1.36 million confirmed cases, now represents 32.7% of the global cases of COVID-19. A global total of 283 859 deaths have been reported, with 279 226 (98.4%) outside mainland China.

In descending rank order, the USA is number 1 for numbers of confirmed cases of COVID-19, Spain is number 2, and the UK is number 3, followed by Italy, Russia, France, Germany, Brazil, Turkey, and Iran as number 10. China is now number 11. The UK has now moved to 3rd place with Italy going into 4th place in terms of cumulative case numbers. The USA reported the highest number of newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours (20 329), followed by Russia (11 012), followed by Brazil (6638) and the UK reporting the 4th-highest 24-hour newly confirmed cases (3923). - Mod.MPP]

